Here’s what changed.

### `DetailPanelShell` now uses `CoverView`

All three detail panels (`plot-detail-panel`, `profile-detail-panel`, `criterion-detail-panel`) only use `DetailPanelShell`, so updating `detail-panel-chrome.tsx` updates every detail panel at once.

```1:36:apps/frontend-web/src/panels/detail-panel-chrome.tsx
import { CoverView, IconButton, usePanelsContext } from "@portugal/ui";
import { X } from "lucide-react";
import type { ReactNode } from "react";

export function DetailPanelCloseButton({ panelType }: { panelType: string }) {
	const { removePanel } = usePanelsContext();
	return (
		<IconButton
			icon={X}
			aria-label="Close panel"
			onClick={() => removePanel(panelType)}
		/>
	);
}

export function DetailPanelShell({
	title,
	panelType,
	children,
}: {
	title: string;
	panelType: string;
	children: ReactNode;
}) {
	return (
		<CoverView
			className="h-full min-h-0"
			colorScheme="background"
			title={title}
			secondaryAction={<DetailPanelCloseButton panelType={panelType} />}
			contentClassName="space-y-4 pr-1 text-sm"
		>
			{children}
		</CoverView>
	);
}
```

**Details:**

- **Chrome:** Replaced `Card` / `CardHeader` / `CardContent` with `CoverView` from `@portugal/ui` (sewdn), matching [COVERVIEW_AI_GUIDE.md](packages/ui/src/components/sewdn/CoverView/COVERVIEW_AI_GUIDE.md).
- **Close control:** Still `IconButton` with `X`, now in `secondaryAction` (top-right). `invertColors` was removed for `colorScheme="background"` without a cover image, as in the guide.
- **Layout:** `className="h-full min-h-0"` so height works inside flex panel layouts; default `scrollable` keeps `ScrollArea` for body content (replacing the old `max-h` + `overflow-y-auto` on the card).
- **Body:** `contentClassName` keeps `space-y-4`, `text-sm`, and right padding so content matches the previous spacing.

`bun run build` in `apps/frontend-web` completes successfully.

[REDACTED]

